<div data-ajax-modal="container">
  <div class="modal-header">
    <button type="button" class="ajax-modal-close close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Ã—</button>
    <h1 class="modal-title"><%= t('help.searching') %></h1>
  </div>
  <div class="modal-body">
    <ul class="advanced-help">
      <li>Select "match all" to require all fields.
      </li>

      <li>Select "match any" to find at least one field.
      </li>

      <li>Combine keywords and attributes to find specific items.
      </li>

      <li>Use quotation marks to search as a phrase.

      <li>Use "+" before a term to make it required. (Otherwise results matching
        only some of your terms may be included).
      </li>

      <li>Use "-" before a word or phrase to exclude.

      <li>Use "OR", "AND", and "NOT" to create complex boolean logic. You can
        use parentheses in your complex expressions.
      </li>
      <li>Truncation and wildcards are not supported - word-stemming is done
        automatically.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>